&lt;p&gt;Noom is on a mission to help people live better, longer. We&#39;re a consumer-led digital health company, connecting people to content, coaching, community, and clinicians, to build lasting habits and live healthier lives. We&#39;re a high-growth organization powered by science, technology, and world-class talent. When you join Noom, on any team, you&#39;ll see the impact of your work on the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Design Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design at Noom sits at the intersection of behavior change science and everyday product experience. Our design system is the backbone that lets us move fast without sacrificing quality across a growing, multi-platform product suite, and this team is redefining how design and engineering collaborate at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role (Contract)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;3-month contract role&lt;/strong&gt; (35-40 hrs/week) to accelerate the maturity of Noom&#39;s design system. You&#39;ll build a token structure that works cleanly across platforms, prepare our design system for AI tools, and close the gap between what&#39;s designed in Figma and what&#39;s actually built in code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale design systems in Figma at a senior/staff level, including components, variants, and token architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring deep expertise in platform design standards (Material Design, Apple HIG, Liquid Glass) and know when to deviate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design token and component structures that translate cleanly into code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with engineers on Code Connect, linking Figma components to their code counterparts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on structuring our design system so AI tools can use it reliably (docs, MD/JSON files)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor designers on semantic tokens and proper component-building&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on a governance model for versioning, contributing, and retiring system updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide how a brand refresh rolls through the token layer without rebuilding every component&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re interested in shaping the future of health by building the design systems foundation that lets great design ship reliably at scale, this role may be for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Played a significant role in shipping, rebuilding, or advancing a large design system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep hands-on experience with agentic design and what design system/brand gaps matter most for AI results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Judgment on when Figma vs. code should be the source of truth, component by component&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnosed and fixed real Figma-to-production inconsistencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong judgment on component architecture and token architecture (primitive, semantic, component-level), including light/dark and brand theming&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience helping a design team actually adopt a new system, not just document one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes This Job Amazing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your work directly shapes how millions of people experience a product built to help them build healthier habits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll help solve an emerging problem in design: making a design system legible and reliable for AI tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll shape governance and structure to keep the system running smoothly and scale into the future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
